</HL>
<DATE>
04/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LATAM
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The International Monetary Fund approved a
$111 million loan to Trinidad and Tobago to support its
economic-reform efforts.
   The IMF said an additional $55 million loan may be
available later to meet unexpected developments, such as a
decline in the county's oil-export earnings or higher
interest rates.
</LP>
