<LP>
   EL MONTE, Calif. -- Vons Cos. posted first-quarter net
income of $15.2 million, or 39 cents a share, compared with a
net loss of $13.4 million, or 35 cents a share, a year
earlier.
   The retail supermarket chain said the latest net included
an extraordinary gain of $7 million, or 18 cents a share,
from a tax-loss carry-forward. Sales rose 3%, to $1.2 billion
from $1.1 billion.
