   New Securities Issues
</HL>
<DATE>
04/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C23
</SO>
<CO>
   F.CN EUROP JAPAN J.DWB
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<GV>
FEDERAL GOVERNMENT (FDL)
</GV>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report:
                                                                                                       

                         MUNICIPALS
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   State Environmental Improvement and Energy Resources
Authority, Missouri -- $60 million of environmental
improvement revenue bonds, Union Electric Co. project, Series
1990 A, due May 1, 2020, were priced by a Goldman, Sachs &amp;
Co. group to yield 7.57% in 2020. The single tranche of 7.40%
bonds is priced at 98 and rated single-A-2 by Moody's
Investors Service Inc. and single-A by Standard &amp; Poor's
Corp.
                                                                                                       

                            OTHER
                                                                                                       

   Federal Farm Credit Banks -- $250 million of notes, due
May 1, 1994, was priced at par for an initial yield of 9.25%.
The notes will be reoffered at various prices through
underwriters led by Merrill Lynch Capital Markets. The notes,
which are non-callable for two years, were priced at a spread
of 0.35 percentage point above the Treasury's four-year note.
                                                                                                       

                          EUROBONDS
                                                                                                       

   Japan Finance Corp. for Municipal Enterprises (Japan) --
$150 million of 9 3/4% bonds due May 18, 2000, priced at 101
1/4 to yield 9.87% less fees, via Bank of Tokyo Capital
Markets. Guaranteed by the government of Japan. Fees 2.
   Interfinance Credit National N.V. (French parent) -- 500
million French francs ($87.7 million) of 10 1/4% bonds due
May 21, 1993, priced at 101 to yield 10.61% less full fees
via Paribas Capital Markets Ltd. Guaranteed by Credit
National. Fees 1 3/8.
   Daiwa Overseas Finance Ltd. (Japanese parent) -- $67
million of 10% bonds due May 17, 2000, priced at 102 to yield
10%, via Morgan Stanley International. Guaranteed by Daiwa
Bank. Once-only call option at 100 in 1994.
   Heller Financial Inc. -- 10 billion yen ($63.5 million) of
floating-rate notes due June 1995 priced at 100.15 via
Goldman Sachs International Ltd. Interest will be paid at the
six-month London interbank offered rate flat. Callable and
puttable at par on the second, third and fourth anniversaries
of the issue date.
   Kingdom of Spain (sovereign) -- 500 million European
currency units of 10 3/4% bonds due May 22, 1995, priced at
100.20 to yield 11.21% via Banco Bilbao Vizcaya and Banco
Espanol de Credito (Banesto).
