</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C23
</SO>
<CO>
   ADD
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   AMES DEPARTMENT STORES Inc. (Rocky Hill, Conn.) --
Standard &amp; Poor's Corp. said it lowered its rating on $355
million of this discount department store company's
subordinated debt to triple-C-plus from single-B-plus. The
rating concern cited "growing uncertainty" that Ames can
correct violations of its bank credit agreement, as well as
"dimmed" prospects for a turnaround of the company's
operating problems. S&amp;P said Ames's subordinated debt remains
on its CreditWatch list with negative implications.
</LP>
