of London, he will oversee the operations of 1,250 retail
eyewear stores operating under the names Pearle Vision
Centers and Pearle Vision Express.
   Both Southland and Pearle said Mr. Antioco's move isn't
related to Southland's trouble in paying its debt from its
1987 leveraged buy-out or Southland's recent agreement to
sell 75% of its equity to its Japanese partners.
   "We've been courting him for some time," said Howard
Stanworth, Pearle chairman and chief executive officer.
